definition: to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: For the director of music. With stringed instruments.
sentences.chinese: 亚萨的诗歌，交与伶长，用丝弦的乐器。

sentences.english: He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was wroth with his inheritance.
sentences.chinese: 并将他的百姓交与刀剑，向他的产业发怒。

sentences.english: Come to LiYuan home, the father will write letters to LiYuan hands.
sentences.chinese: 来到李渊家中，如意将父亲写的信件交与李渊手中。

sentences.english: The letter has been given to person concerned.
For the Father judges no man, but has committed all judgment to the Son.
sentences.chinese: 父不审判什么人，乃将审判的事全交与子。

sentences.english: Payment by cash to be made only at the Centre.
sentences.chinese: 如以现款支付，请亲临本中心交与负责人。

sentences.english: For the Father judgeth no man, but hath committed all judgment unto the Son
sentences.chinese: 父不审判什么人，乃将审判的事全交与子。

sentences.english: He put the rest of the men under the command of Abishai his brother, and they were deployed against the Ammonites.
sentences.chinese: 其余的兵交与他兄弟亚比筛，对着亚扪人摆阵。

sentences.english: And the rest of the people he delivered into the hand of Abishai his brother, that he might put them in array against the children of Ammon.
sentences.chinese: 其馀的兵交与他兄弟亚比筛，对着亚扪人摆阵。

sentences.english: For the choir director, with my stringed instruments.
sentences.chinese: 这歌交与歌咏长，用丝弦的乐器。

sentences.english: For the director of music. For Jeduthun. A psalm of David.
sentences.chinese: 大卫的诗，交与伶长耶杜顿。

sentences.english: Unto the end, in verses. A psalm of David.
sentences.chinese: 达味诗歌，交与乐官，和以弦乐。

sentences.english: Unto the end, in verses, a psalm for David, for the octave.
sentences.chinese: 达味诗歌，交与乐官，和以弦乐，八度低音。

definition: to return/to give back/to send back/to repatriate
to pass on to sb/to carry and give to sb else
to hold in safekeeping/to have in one's care/to guarantee/certainly/surely/custodian/curator
to put sb to trouble (of doing sth)/vexation/inconvenience
to inconvenience/to trouble (sb with a request)
variant of 賜予|赐予[ci4 yu3]
arrow banner of command (archaic used as symbol of military authority)/fig. instructions from one's superiors
